nd treasure, which ultimately led them to take over the derelict ship that turned out to be a trap, resulting in their deaths. The narrator, who was the skipper of the Martian Maid, described his crew as men who were proud of their greed and saw themselves as entitled to keep what they could find in space. Despite the risks involved, the crew was eager to examine the derelict starship for potential financial gain, specifically the gold-like metal that made up its hull. However, this decision proved fatal, leading to the demise of the entire crew except for the narrator, who watched as they were reduced to jelly by the six-inch supersonic projector on the derelict ship.">
